################################################################################
# COMMON PATTERNS AND BEST PRACTICES
################################################################################

# Best Practices:
#
# 1. Principle of Least Privilege:
#    - Grant only the specific actions needed (StartSigningJob, GetSigningProfile, etc.)
#    - Use specific IAM roles instead of entire AWS accounts when possible
#    - Consider version-specific permissions for tighter control
#
# 2. Statement ID Management:
#    - Use descriptive statement IDs that indicate the purpose
#    - Use statement_id_prefix when creating multiple similar permissions
#    - Avoid statement_id conflicts by using unique identifiers
#
# 3. Cross-Account Access:
#    - Document which accounts have access and why
#    - Regularly audit cross-account permissions
#    - Use IAM role ARNs for more granular control than account IDs
#
# 4. Version Management:
#    - Specify profile_version for version-specific permissions
#    - Omit profile_version to allow access to all versions
#    - Consider the lifecycle of your signing profiles
#
# 5. Security Considerations:
#    - Limit RevokeSignature permission to trusted principals
#    - Monitor SigningJob operations for unusual activity
#    - Use AWS Organizations SCPs for additional guardrails

# Common Use Cases:
#
# 1. Lambda Code Signing:
#    - Grant deployment account StartSigningJob permission
#    - Allow CI/CD pipelines to sign Lambda code
#
# 2. Multi-Account Organizations:
#    - Enable shared signing profiles across accounts
#    - Centralize code signing in a security account
#
# 3. Third-Party Integration:
#    - Grant external vendors GetSigningProfile permission
#    - Allow partners to verify signature validity
#
# 4. Audit and Compliance:
#    - Grant security teams RevokeSignature permission
#    - Enable compliance tools to read signing profiles

# Troubleshooting:
#
# 1. "ConflictException: Statement already exists":
#    - Check for duplicate statement_id values
#    - Use statement_id_prefix for automatic uniqueness
#
# 2. "AccessDeniedException":
#    - Verify the signing profile exists and is accessible
#    - Check IAM permissions for the Terraform execution role
#
# 3. "InvalidParameterException: Invalid action":
#    - Ensure action is one of the four valid values
#    - Check for typos in the action name
#
# 4. Permission not taking effect:
#    - Verify the principal has the necessary IAM permissions
#    - Check for conflicting deny policies in the target account
#    - Ensure the signing profile is in the same region

